16class DateBuiltinsAssembler : public CodeStubAssembler {
17 public:
18 explicit DateBuiltinsAssembler(compiler::CodeAssemblerState* state)
19 : CodeStubAssembler(state) {}
20
21 protected:
22 void Generate_DatePrototype_GetField(TNode<Context> context,
23 TNode<Object> receiver, int field_index);
24};
25
26void DateBuiltinsAssembler::Generate_DatePrototype_GetField(
27 TNode<Context> context, TNode<Object> receiver, int field_index) {
28 Label receiver_not_date(this, Label::kDeferred);
29
30 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(receiver), &receiver_not_date);
31 TNode<Uint16T> receiver_instance_type = LoadInstanceType(CAST(receiver));
32 GotoIfNot(InstanceTypeEqual(receiver_instance_type, JS_DATE_TYPE),
33 &receiver_not_date);
34
35 TNode<JSDate> date_receiver = CAST(receiver);
36 // Load the specified date field, falling back to the runtime as necessary.
37 if (field_index == JSDate::kDateValue) {
38 Return(LoadObjectField(date_receiver, JSDate::kValueOffset));
39 } else {
40 if (field_index < JSDate::kFirstUncachedField) {
41 Label stamp_mismatch(this, Label::kDeferred);
42 TNode<Object> date_cache_stamp = Load<Object>(
43 ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::date_cache_stamp(isolate())));
44
45 TNode<Object> cache_stamp =
46 LoadObjectField(date_receiver, JSDate::kCacheStampOffset);
47 GotoIf(TaggedNotEqual(date_cache_stamp, cache_stamp), &stamp_mismatch);
48 Return(LoadObjectField(date_receiver,
49 JSDate::kValueOffset + field_index * kTaggedSize));
50
51 BIND(&stamp_mismatch);
52 }
53
54 TNode<ExternalReference> isolate_ptr =
55 ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::isolate_address(isolate()));
56 TNode<Smi> field_index_smi = SmiConstant(field_index);
57 TNode<ExternalReference> function =
58 ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::get_date_field_function());
59 TNode<Object> result = CAST(CallCFunction(
60 function, MachineType::AnyTagged(),
61 std::make_pair(MachineType::Pointer(), isolate_ptr),
62 std::make_pair(MachineType::AnyTagged(), date_receiver),
63 std::make_pair(MachineType::AnyTagged(), field_index_smi)));
64 Return(result);
65 }
66
67 // Raise a TypeError if the receiver is not a date.
68 BIND(&receiver_not_date);
69 { ThrowTypeError(context, MessageTemplate::kNotDateObject); }
70}

186TF_BUILTIN(DatePrototypeToPrimitive, CodeStubAssembler) {
187 auto context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);
188 auto receiver = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kReceiver);
189 auto hint = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kHint);
190
191 // Check if the {receiver} is actually a JSReceiver.
192 Label receiver_is_invalid(this, Label::kDeferred);
193 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(receiver), &receiver_is_invalid);
194 GotoIfNot(JSAnyIsNotPrimitive(CAST(receiver)), &receiver_is_invalid);
195
196 // Dispatch to the appropriate OrdinaryToPrimitive builtin.
197 Label hint_is_number(this), hint_is_string(this),
198 hint_is_invalid(this, Label::kDeferred);
199
200 // Fast cases for internalized strings.
201 TNode<String> number_string = NumberStringConstant();
202 GotoIf(TaggedEqual(hint, number_string), &hint_is_number);
203 TNode<String> default_string = DefaultStringConstant();
204 GotoIf(TaggedEqual(hint, default_string), &hint_is_string);
205 TNode<String> string_string = StringStringConstant();
206 GotoIf(TaggedEqual(hint, string_string), &hint_is_string);
207
208 // Slow-case with actual string comparisons.
209 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(hint), &hint_is_invalid);
210 GotoIfNot(IsString(CAST(hint)), &hint_is_invalid);
211
212 TNode<IntPtrT> hint_length = LoadStringLengthAsWord(CAST(hint));
213 GotoIfStringEqual(CAST(hint), hint_length, number_string, &hint_is_number);
214 GotoIfStringEqual(CAST(hint), hint_length, default_string, &hint_is_string);
215 GotoIfStringEqual(CAST(hint), hint_length, string_string, &hint_is_string);
216 Goto(&hint_is_invalid);
217
218 // Use the OrdinaryToPrimitive builtin to convert to a Number.
219 BIND(&hint_is_number);
220 {
221 Builtin builtin =
222 Builtins::OrdinaryToPrimitive(OrdinaryToPrimitiveHint::kNumber);
223 TNode<Object> result = CallBuiltin(builtin, context, receiver);
224 Return(result);
225 }
226
227 // Use the OrdinaryToPrimitive builtin to convert to a String.
228 BIND(&hint_is_string);
229 {
230 Builtin builtin =
231 Builtins::OrdinaryToPrimitive(OrdinaryToPrimitiveHint::kString);
232 TNode<Object> result = CallBuiltin(builtin, context, receiver);
233 Return(result);
234 }
235
236 // Raise a TypeError if the {hint} is invalid.
237 BIND(&hint_is_invalid);
238 { ThrowTypeError(context, MessageTemplate::kInvalidHint, hint); }
239
240 // Raise a TypeError if the {receiver} is not a JSReceiver instance.
241 BIND(&receiver_is_invalid);
242 {
243 ThrowTypeError(context, MessageTemplate::kIncompatibleMethodReceiver,
244 StringConstant("Date.prototype [ @@toPrimitive ]"),
245 receiver);
246 }
